<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPPERS-NOTES-LBPT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JOHNSON LIKES HIS SUMMER JOB
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SEAN KEARNS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Clippers began their summer league mini-camp on Friday -
with a coaching vacancy still hanging over the franchise's head.
Not that people don't want the job.
</P>
<P>
   Dennis Johnson woke up Friday morning at 5:30, excited to be the
summer league coach for the Clippers. Without a coach since the end
of last season, Johnson, a candidate to fill the spot, has been
assigned to lead the team of 13 players.
</P>
<P>
   For two hours Friday morning, Johnson, in sweatpants and a
T-shirt, led the summer league Clippers through the team's first
mini-camp practice, going over defensive and offensive plans.
</P>
<P>
   Afterward Johnson said he felt ``pretty dog gone good'' about
being the man running the team.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I got up this morning it was at 5:30, it wasn't because
of nervousness,'' Johnson said. ``It was because I was at the helm
and a head coach. Again, it may be for the summer it may not
be..We'd all like perfect situations but there's still only 29 of
these jobs, actually there is only two of these jobs (the Clippers
and Pacers have openings). You do what can to impress the people
you need to impress and then you go on from there.''
</P>
<P>
   Elgin Baylor, vice president of basketball operations, said that
he has narrowed his list of candidates down to at least five but
gave no names or timeframe for the selection of a coach. He said
Johnson is still a candidate. John Lucas, an assistant with the
Denver Nuggets, has been championed by agent David Falk for the
position.
</P>
<P>
   While Baylor and Johnson balked at calling the summer league
coaching job an audition, both said it was a chance for Johnson to
show his skills as a coach.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it will help to give an idea of what he can do as far
as running the team,'' said Elgin Baylor, vice president of
basketball operations. ``It would be a good indication of how well
he works with the players and his organization as a coach, his
style, his technique. There are various different things you find
out about his coaching ability.''
</P>
<P>
   Baylor said that his evaluation of Johnson had been ongoing.
While Johnson said he wants to show Baylor what he can do at the
position, the two hadn't spoke specifically about any evaluations .
</P>
<P>
   ``My interaction with guys is whatever it is,'' Johnson said.
``It's never been a question. If that's basis of hiring you might
as well do it right now. I think my interaction is very good.
</P>
<P>
   ``My skill on the court, and I know better than anybody, I
haven't been a coach in the NBA but I have prepared myself for this
by going through assistant to assistant to assistant and then being
a head coach in the CBA. I've very confident with myself.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson was an assistant with the Boston Celtics for four
seasons. Before becoming an assistant with the Clippers in the
middle of last season, Johnson was the coach for the LaCrosse
Bobcats in the CBA. As a player Johnson was a three-time NBA
champion with the Seattle Supersonics and Boston Celtics, playing
in a total of five NBA finals.Johnson could be an assistant if he
loses out on the head coaching position, but that choice would be
up to the new coach, Baylor said. For the time being Johnson isn't
thinking that way.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't gave (being an assistant) any thought,'' Johnson
said. ``I think its almost like a fighter's syndrome. If you are
thinking like a sparing partner you are going to go out on the mat
like a sparing partner. I'm thinking like a head coach. If I happen
to get whooped its going to be by a knockout.''
</P>
<P>
   DRAFT PICKS NOT IN CAMP
</P>
<P>
   The lack of a coach has limited the Clippers. First round draft
picks Darius Miles, Keyon Dooling and Quentin Richardson will not
be at the mini-camp and probably not at the summer league citing
the lack of a head coach.
</P>
<P>
   Other NBA teams have their first round draft picks in camp. The
Dallas Mavericks, who also ended up with three first round picks,
have all three on their summer league roster.
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers had two free agent rookies in camp on Friday, North
Carolina point guard Ed Cota and Delaware center Ndongo N'Diaye.
</P>
<P>
   MAGGETTE AND STRONG IN L.A.
</P>
<P>
   Swingman Corey Maggette and power forward Derek Strong passed
their physicals on Friday, completing the draft day trade that sent
the two and Dooling to the Clippers for a lottery-protected
first-round draft pick.
</P>
<P>
   Maggette, an athletic 6-foot-6, 215-pounds, had planned on
playing with Orlando in the Summer Pro League at the Pyramid. But
with the trade, he decided to play and workout in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
   Maggette said he benefited in his rookie season last year from
the guidance of Magic coach Doc Rivers and said the best coach for
the Clippers would be someone who favors an uptempo style.
</P>
<P>
   ``We need a coach that wants it like we do, kind of like a
player coach like Doc was, someone who knows our guys strengths and
knows our weakness and knows what we can do to achieve our goals
that we set for ourselves,'' Maggette said. ``By looking at our
team, we are a team who can really run on the floor. With Lamar
(Odom) he is a great ball handler and shooter, he's a great
all-around player..plus you are going to have guys running the
wings with him that can help him out.''
</P>
<P>
   Strong, a 6-9, 240-pound power forward, is making his second
return to Los Angeles. Strong, who went to Pacific Palisades High
School, played the 1995-96 season with the Lakers. Strong will be
playing in the summer league but not with the Clippers.
</P>
<P>
   SKINNER BACK
</P>
<P>
   Brian Skinner returned to the practice court on Friday, after
missing the last 26 games, and 43 games overall, with a high ankle
sprain.
</P>
<P>
   The long holdout wasn't due to any complications with the
injury, just the need for rest and more rehabilitation, Skinner
said. ``It's still sore a little bit playing on it trying to back
into rigors of it,'' Skinner said.
</P>
<P>
   Skinner looked comfortable running through drills with the team.
</P>
<P>
   ``It looks like he is in pretty good shape,'' Baylor said ``He
looks healthy it looks like his ankle is fine. I watched him run
and jump and move..as far as his mobility it was very good.
</P>
<P>
   ODDS AND ENDS
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers waived point guard Charles Jones on Friday. Jones
averaged 3.4 points and 1.7 assists per game last season..Former
UCLA star Charles O'Bannon was added to the Clipper summer league
roster. He played last season in Poland...Baylor said that the
Clippers are talking with teams and agents about offseason deals.
For right now the Clippers are over the salary cap and would need
to renounce some free agents. Without free agents Maurice Taylor
and Derek Anderson, the Clippers would have more than $5 million in
cap space.
</P>
<P>
   Clipper forward Etdrick Bohannon didn't practice with the
Clippers Friday and underwent an MRI on his left knee. The results
will be back on Monday. Bohannon, signed through 2001, hurt himself
during offseason workouts.
</P>
</TEXT>
