<SLUG> BC-COVER0709-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Designer finds success creating covers for digital assistants
 &HT;    By Meredith Moss
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ The idea seems obvious, so why didn't anyone
think of it before ?
</P>
<P>
   ``Women get to accessorize with great shoes and handbags, so why
shouldn't our Palm Pilot covers and planners express who we are and
be fabulous also?'' asks Sunny Knox.
</P>
<P>
   The Dayton native, who now makes her home in Los Angeles,
theorized that women would be anxious to replace ``black and
boring'' accessory covers with those more funky and fashionable.
</P>
<P>
   She figured right. Today Sunshine Knox (her business card simply
reads ``Sunshine'') is the president and designer of Sunny Kate, a
1-year-old company that's already sold thousands of items and is
quickly becoming known for its upscale accessories for women.
</P>
<P>
   Knox, 28, has been acting and modeling since Dayton days and
moved to L.A. when a talent scout recruited her from OSU. She's
since appeared in commercials, in skits on ``The Tonight Show with
Jay Leno'' and on television series such as ``Beverly Hills
90210.'' Her twin brother, Adam Doench, is also in L.A., working as
a television and film director.
</P>
<P>
   ``Being an actress, I always had my black planner out and I
thought it was so boring!'' she recalls.
</P>
<P>
   Her line of accessories, sold at some of the nation's hippest
boutiques, includes Palm Pilot and laptop computer covers,
checkbook covers and CD cases. There are planners in three sizes,
journals, wallets and photo books. In the works are cell phone
covers.
</P>
<P>
   Knox's products are handmade by American craftsmen and fashioned
from the same upscale fabrics you'll see on runways throughout the
world _ faux fur and raw silk, animal and camouflage prints, comic
strips and floral motifs, with cashmere pockets.
</P>
<P>
   Her biggest seller is a hot pink raw silk with sweetheart rose
trim and a camouflage interior.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's sweet on the outside but it's 'I'll kill you if I have to
on the inside,' `` explains Knox. ``Women have that diversity to
them _ we're sweet and tough, wacky and sophisticated and classy. I
wanted to embody all those things.''
</P>
<P>
   Celebrities _ Brooke Shields, Leeza Gibbons, Daisy Fuentes _
have purchased the products; Donny and Marie Osmond highlighted the
Sunny Kate Palm Pilot Cover on their talk show as the ``gift you
give someone who has everything!'' In April, Accessories magazine
showed off the line.
</P>
<P>
   The company got another boost when Knox was contacted by Melanie
Griffith, who loved the designs and wanted to join Knox in
developing a line of laptop covers.
</P>
<P>
   Goddess by Melanie Griffith, introduced at the New York
stationery show in May, is a ``laptop skin'' that aims to dress up
a portable computer without the cover needing to be removed before
use. The product, designed by Knox, includes space to carry cables,
CDs and papers, features a shoulder strap and access panel for cord
connection, and is available in six Sunny Kate fabrics.
</P>
<P>
   The CEO of Sunny Kate is Matthew Knox, Sunny's husband, whom she
describes as ``the wind beneath my sales.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm the artist, he's the business person,'' she explains.
</P>
<P>
   The line is sold at boutiques such as Fred Segal and Jennifer
Kaufman, both in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think Sunny and Matt were clever because they saw a niche
and filled it,'' says Kaufman, who caters to the television and
film crowd. ``Before we carried the pieces, women would come in and
want something unusual in a datebook but their options were
limited.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sunny Kate line was an immediate hit with Kaufman's
customers.
</P>
<P>
   ``They are completely charming . . . people buy them as we're
stocking the displays,'' Kaufman says. ``I traded in a typical
checkbook cover for one of Sunny's and every time I take my new one
out _ at my daughter's school or at the bank _ someone asks me
where it's from because it's so cool!''
</P>
<P>
   ``I've seen those lip prints on runways in London,'' Kaufman
says, referring to the Sunny Kate red-lips-on-black design. ``Sunny
picked up on it and I know you'll be seeing that motif. She has
prints suited to every woman's personality.''
</P>
<P>
   Prices range from $24 for a checkbook cover to $150 for the
laptop skin.
</P>
<P>
   Knox recently was in town for a friend's wedding and says she
always heads back to Ohio for the Ohio State-Michigan game. She
says it's her job to be one step ahead and to forecast what will be
``great and outrageous and awesome'' in the future.
</P>
<P>
   Concludes the young entrepreneur:''I always try to stay one step
ahead.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
