<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
 TAKE-KAN   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DIANE CARROLL  
<TEXT>
<P>
   (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) a receding hairline.''
</P>
<P>
   Vicki said she sent Robinson a candid shot of herself fully
dressed in a skirt and white sweater. Robinson asked for a photo of
her naked. She complied.
</P>
<P>
   The two pictures she e-mailed him are now in the hands of
detectives who are investigating Robinson, Vicki said, according to
a detective she spoke with.
</P>
<P>
   Sgt. Rick Roth of Lenexa said Friday that a detective did
interview Vicki but that he could not comment further.
</P>
<P>
   In retrospect, she said, it was ``kind of silly'' of her to
become Robinson's slave when they had not even met. But she kept
thinking they would meet.
</P>
<P>
   As his slave, Vicki provided Robinson with her daily schedule,
as he demanded. ``He wanted to know where I was all the time,'' she
said.
</P>
<P>
   She needed his permission to attend
bondage-discipline-sadomasochism, or BDSM, events. And she was not
allowed to let anyone touch her body.
</P>
<P>
   ``He made sure that I knew that my body was his,'' she said.
``That's part of being a slave. You understand that.''
</P>
<P>
   Most people don't understand BDSM, she said. They think there's
something psychologically wrong with anyone who wants to be
controlled and gets pleasure from pain.
</P>
<P>
   ``But I think I am a very stable, well-balanced person. ... I'm
a very strong person,'' she said. ``I run my own business. I am a
nurse, I do reflexology and I'm very much in control there.
</P>
<P>
   ``For me to give that control over the rest of my life to
someone, it's like taking a holiday. I don't have to make
decisions. I don't have to be responsible. That person is
responsible for what I do.''
</P>
<P>
   It's possible her mother unwittingly played a part in
encouraging her submissive side, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Even as a toddler, she said, ``I was a very wild child.'' To
control her, her mother put her in a harness and hooked her up to a
clothesline. ``When we went camping, she had me on a harness and we
would go for walks.''
</P>
<P>
   When she was about 14, she said, she began writing stories on a
typewriter _ stories about being kidnapped. She also started
drawing pictures of torture gadgets such as a stretching rack.
</P>
<P>
   ``I must have read a book or watched movies, and my wild
imagination kind of grew,'' she said. ``As I got older, I found
some magazines.''
</P>
<P>
   Vicki said she tried a traditional heterosexual relationship.
</P>
<P>
   ``My mother loved this boy,'' she said. `He would do anything,
absolutely anything, for me. Whatever I wanted was OK. I hated it.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wanted someone to make some decisions. I always have this
feeling that a man should be a man. I don't mean cruel and mean and
that type of thing, but I think he should be in charge.''
</P>
<P>
   A slave-master relationship requires more trust than a
traditional relationship, she said. A slave has to be certain that
her master will treat her well because the master has so much
control.
</P>
<P>
   The idea of being branded is ``kind of scary,'' she said. But
she can understand why a master might want to brand a slave because
``it's a symbol of being owned.''
</P>
<P>
   Vicki said she became frustrated with Robinson because he always
came up with some excuse about why they couldn't meet before living
together.
</P>
<P>
   Eventually, she met a new master on the Internet site where she
had met Robinson. He lives closer to her, she said, and has met her
family. They plan to marry, she said.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson was upset when she told him she had met someone new,
she said.
</P>
<P>
   He told her she was not worthy to be his slave, she said. Then
he said it didn't matter anyway because he'd found a new slave: a
19-year-old coming over from France.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities have not said anything about a Robinson link with a
French 19-year-old, and Vicki realizes she has no way of knowing
whether the woman existed.
</P>
<P>
   From what she knows of Robinson now, she said, he is ``a really,
really good liar.'' ( 30 )
</P>
</TEXT>
