<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NY-POLICE-SUSPEND-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OFF-DUTY POLICE OFFICER SUSPENDED FOR FIRING GUN 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ An off-duty police detective fired a single shot from
his fifth-floor apartment window at a gunman who was confronting
another man in the street and who had ignored the detective's order
to drop the gun, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The detective, Robert Lopez, was suspended for discharging his
firearm in a reckless manner, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Because the incident occurred at the officer's apartment
building, the police would not provide the address.
</P>
<P>
   Lopez said he saw a group of men in front of his building late
Friday night, one of them with a gun, the police said. The
detective yelled from the window, ordering the man to drop the
weapon, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   When the man refused to drop the gun, Lopez fired a single shot,
dispersing the group, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   One of the men, Andre Tull, 25, was arrested a few blocks away
and charged with possession of a weapon and menacing, although no
gun was found, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   Lopez is assigned to the 106th Precinct detective squad, which
covers the Ozone Park and Howard Beach sections of Queens County.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
